column2: George W. Bush: "If you've retired, you don't have anything to worry about. It's the third time I've said that. I'll probably say it three more times. See, in my line of work you got to keep repeating things over and over and over again for the truth to sink in, to kind of catapult the propaganda."
Phil Davison: "Tell your friends, tell your neighbors, tell Randy Gonzales, I'm comin'."
